        "subject": "LU-432 Fixes error: ‘struct sock’ has no member named ‘sk_sleep’",
        "message": "LU-432 Fixes error: ‘struct sock’ has no member named ‘sk_sleep’\n\nStarting from kernel 2.6.35 sock struct don't include the sk_sleep\nfield. Instead there is the sk_sleep() function to provide this\ninformation. This checks whether the sock struct provide directly\nsupport for sk_sleep and if not uses the sk_sleep() function.\n\nChange-Id: I86a40f2117d1c342f04575979f3a9715552d6bc7\nSigned-off-by: Christos Triantafyllidis <ctria@grid.auth.gr>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
